# React Frontend Standards

## Component structure
- Functional components only. No class components.
- One component per file. File name matches component name (`KPICard.tsx` exports `KPICard`).
- Pages in `pages/`, reusable UI in `components/{charts,cards,controls,layout,tables}/`.
- Use `AppLayout` with `LeftSidebar`, `RightSidebar`, `BottomPanel` for page scaffolding.

## Naming
- Components: PascalCase (`EquityCurve`, `KPIPanel`).
- Props interfaces: `{ComponentName}Props` (`EquityCurveProps`).
- Hooks: `use` prefix (`useReplayStore`, `useBacktestQuery`).
- Event handlers: `on` prefix (`onRunBacktest`, `onDateChange`).
- Booleans: `is`/`has`/`should` prefix (`isLoading`, `hasError`).
- API functions: verb + resource (`fetchEquityCurve`, `runBacktest`).

## Data fetching
- Use TanStack Query for all API calls. No raw `fetch` in components.
- API client methods live in `lib/api.ts`. Types in `lib/types.ts`.
- Never duplicate type definitions — single source of truth in `types.ts`.

## Styling (hedge-fund terminal aesthetic)
- Background: `bg-zinc-950` (page), `bg-zinc-900` (panels).
- Text: `text-zinc-100` (primary), `text-zinc-400` (secondary), `text-zinc-500` (labels).
- Semantics: `text-emerald-400` positive, `text-red-400` negative, `text-blue-400` neutral.
- Numbers: always `font-mono tabular-nums` (JetBrains Mono).
- Charts: transparent backgrounds, zinc axes, 2-3 semantic colors max.
- No shadows, no gradients, no rounded-xl. Minimal borders (`border-zinc-800`).

## Do NOT
- Put quant math or strategy logic in TypeScript — API only.
- Use `any` type — define proper interfaces.
- Create god components > 300 lines — extract hooks and sub-components.
- Add external UI libraries (no MUI, no Chakra) — Tailwind only.
